sentences: Ta on teeninud palju kogemusi tööga.
Ma olen teeninud hea maine oma professionaalsusega.
Lapsed on teeninud väga head punktid eksamitel.
context: Teeninud is the past tense/participle form of the verb 'teenima' in Estonian. It means to earn, gain, or make something through effort, work, or achievement. The word can refer to earning money/income, gaining experience/knowledge/experience, or achieving success/results.
